metadata.name: The Birth of Venus
metadata.description:
Digital work of art based on the famous Boticcelli painting through the use of tools for the digitalization of the work and its subsequent destruction through algorithms and coordinates to build a new avant-garde model that lives between abstraction and Dadaism. In addition, this work has been painted in oil in real life.

In the words of Tristan Tzara: "I have an insane and uncontrollable desire to murder the beauty..."
